posts.name: Wihy
posts.cooked:
Hello! Recently, I began work on implementing AdvantageKit in our code. However, I’ve encountered a strange problem. Advantage kit doesn’t generate the AutoLogged class in the build folder.

I looked at this thread, but it was of no help to me

AdvantageKit AutoLog annotation not generating InpustAutoLogged subsystems Programming

This is my code. CodeAkit 881×331 38.1 KB

CodeAkit 881×331 38.1 KB

CodeAkit 881×331 38.1 KB

I’m running Build robot but the class doesn’t appears under the build folder I’ve also tried deleting the build folder but to no avail

Are there any hidden requirements for using the @AutoLog notation? Something in Robot.java ?

Currently, the class it’s inside, SwerveModuleIO , isn’t used anywhere. However, quick testing showed that even if it’s used it doesn’t generate. So I don’t think that’s the problem

Thank you in advance

link_counts.title: AdvantageKit AutoLog annotation not generating InpustAutoLogged subsystems

posts.name: Ryan Blue
posts.cooked: How did you set up Advantagekit? If you’re not using one of the sample projects, did you add the annotation processor as directed in the documentation ?

posts.name: viggy96
posts.cooked: Did you add the appropriate dependencies in your build.gradle?

posts.name: Wihy
posts.cooked:
Thanks for the replies I used the skeleton project as a base and added my own code onto that Here’s a link to the class

I don’t recall adding anything as a dependency. Is it needed with the skeleton project?

posts.name: Wihy
posts.cooked: Upon double checking I realized I actually didn’t have the dependency! It now works. thanks!

posts.name: Marcus
posts.cooked: Hey, I’m having the same issue of not getting a generated InputsAutoLogged file, and this is with using the advantagekit base swerve project. I even checked the gradle files to make sure it matches the documentation. For some reason, this only showed up overnight after I restarted my laptop. Furthermore, the included flywheel subsystem now underlines the FlywheelInputsAutoLogged in red even though that file exists in the generated folder. This, however, does not occur with the moduleio or gyroio inputs, in which the InputsAutoLogged files are genereated and still exist.

posts.name: Marcus
posts.cooked: As for the FlywheelIOInputsAutoLogged file, it appears under the generated folder in vscode, but when i look for it in file explorer, it is gone.
